From: AurealNix T527 <juanmanuellopezcarrillo@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 03:12:14 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 099/106] =?UTF-8?q?arm64:=20dts:=20sun55i-t527-orangepi-4a?=
 =?UTF-8?q?:=20OPP=20m=C3=ADnima=20a=20480=20MHz?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Los PLL de CPU se modelan como 24 MHz * N con N >= 20 y el divisor P
del firmware a /1, así que 408 MHz (el mínimo del BSP, que lo alcanza
vía P) no es alcanzable: el reloj redondearía a 480 MHz mientras
cpufreq informaría 408. Se sube la OPP mínima de ambos clusters a
480 MHz reales. El voltaje se mantiene en 0.90 V, dentro del sobre del
BSP (408 y 672 MHz van a 0.90 V en todos los speed bins).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 .../boot/dts/allwinner/sun55i-t527-orangepi-4a.dts | 14 ++++++++++----
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun55i-t527-orangepi-4a.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun55i-t527-orangepi-4a.dts
index 7dcfd6258..d7248287c 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun55i-t527-orangepi-4a.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun55i-t527-orangepi-4a.dts
@@ -241,13 +241,19 @@ / {
 	 * safe on any chip. Capped conservatively for bring-up (little cluster
 	 * at its 1.416 GHz max, big cluster at 1.488 GHz; the big cluster can
 	 * go to ~2 GHz later once reg_dcdc1_323's max is raised past 1.15 V).
+	 *
+	 * The lowest point is 480 MHz instead of the vendor's 408 MHz: the
+	 * CPU PLLs are modelled as plain 24 MHz * N (N >= 20, post-divider
+	 * left at /1 by the firmware), so 480 MHz is the real floor. Its
+	 * 0.90 V sits within the vendor envelope (408 and 672 MHz both run
+	 * at 0.90 V on every speed bin).
 	 */
 	cluster0_opp: opp-table-cluster0 {
 		compatible = "operating-points-v2";
 		opp-shared;
 
-		opp-408000000 {
-			opp-hz = /bits/ 64 <408000000>;
+		opp-480000000 {
+			opp-hz = /bits/ 64 <480000000>;
 			opp-microvolt = <900000>;
 		};
 
@@ -276,8 +282,8 @@ cluster1_opp: opp-table-cluster1 {
 		compatible = "operating-points-v2";
 		opp-shared;
 
-		opp-408000000 {
-			opp-hz = /bits/ 64 <408000000>;
+		opp-480000000 {
+			opp-hz = /bits/ 64 <480000000>;
 			opp-microvolt = <900000>;
 		};
 
